Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Thinly slice the @Closed Cup Mushrooms{150}(thinly sliced). Roughly chop the @Coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and halve the @Lime{1/2}(zested and halved).

Trim the @Aubergine{1}(trimmed), then halve lengthways. Cut into roughly 3cm pieces.

Pop the aubergine onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season with @salt and @pepper then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and golden, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Pour the @Water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Heat a #medium frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @Cashew Nuts{25} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}. TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Once toasted, transfer to a #bowl{} and set aside. Pop your (now empty) pan back on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.

Once the pan is hot, add the mushrooms and stir-fry until golden brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and @Massaman Curry Paste{50} and cook for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @Coconut Milk{200}, @Water{150%ml} for the sauce, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10} and @Peanut Butter{30}.

Stir thoroughly to combine and bring to the boil, then lower the heat to medium-low and simmer until the liquid has reduced by half, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Remove the roasted aubergine from your oven and add to the curry sauce. Once thickened, remove the curry from the heat, then squeeze in the lime juice and stir in half the coriander. Taste and season with salt, pepper and more lime juice if needed.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the lime zest, then spoon into your #bowls{}.

Top with the aubergine curry and sprinkle over the cashews and remaining coriander to finish. Enjoy!

> Step 5 MOD: If you've chosen to add king prawns to your meal, add @?King Prawns{150} to the curry midway through simmering. Boil for the remaining time, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.